Distribution . The species is common throughout a great number of ecoregions of the Western Triangle Province (i.e, Banda Sea, Lesser Sunda, Palawan/ North Borneo , Southern Java, Sulawesi Sea/Makassar Strait) (
Fig. 2
). Also known from adjacent provinces (Java Transitional, (Naturalis collections), Tropical Western Pacific (Coral Reef Research Foundation collections), Northeast Australian Shelf (Queensland Museum collections). The species type locality is King Island, Tasmania, Australia and it was recorded for the Indian Ocean by previous authors (see under list of synonyms). It is found from 4–30 m depth.
